994893659,kitti-to-yolo,joelibaceta/kitti-to-yolo,"This Python script converts the KITTI dataset format into the YOLOv5/YOLOv8 compatible format (images + annotations in .txt, plus a data.yaml).","dataset, kitti, kitty-dataset, yolo",Python,Python,1,0,1,0,2025-06-02T16:38:17Z,2025-07-04T21:19:39Z,2025-06-06T02:17:55Z,MIT License,"# KITTI to YOLO Dataset Converter 🛠️ This Python script converts the KITTI dataset format into the YOLOv5/YOLOv8 compatible format (images + annotations in `.txt`, plus a `data.yaml`). ## 📁 Expected Directory Structure Before running the script, make sure your KITTI data is organized like this: ``` kitti/ ├── training/ │ └── image_2/ │ ├── 000000.png │ ├── 000001.png │ └── … ├── testing/ │ └── image_2/ │ ├── 000100.png │ ├── 000101.png │ └── … └── label/ ├── 000000.txt ├── 000001.txt └── … ``` - `training/image_2/`: training images - `testing/image_2/`: test images (no labels needed) - `label/`: KITTI label files corresponding to `training/image_2/` > 📌 Only objects labeled as `""Car""`, `""Van""`, or `""Truck""` are converted to YOLO format by default. You can customize this in the script. --- ## 🚀 What the Script Does - Converts KITTI bounding boxes to YOLO normalized format - Filters only relevant object classes - Creates the required YOLO directory structure: ``` yolo_dataset/ ├── images"
